QUESTION.QUESTION_DESCRIPTION:
The following code will give
       class Test
       {
			void show()
			{
				System.out.println("non-static method in Test");
			}
       }
       public class Q3 extends Test
       {
			static void show()
			{
				System.out.println("Overridden non-static method in Q3");
			}
			public static void main(String[] args)
			{
				Q3 a = new Q3();
			}
       }

What is the result of the following code :
public class SuperEx {
	String r;
	String s;
	public SuperEx(String a,String b) {
		r = a;
		s = b;
	}
	public void aMethod() {
		System.out.println("r :" + r);
	}
public class NewSuper extends SuperEx {
	public NewSuper(String a,String b) {
	super(a,b);
	}
	public static void main(String args []) {
		SuperEx a = new SuperEx("Hi","Tom");
		SuperEx b = new NewSuper("Hi","Bart");
		a.aMethod();
		b.aMethod();
	}
	public void aMethod() {
	System.out.println("r :" + r + "  s:" + s);
	}
